recommend check-in with Keaton before the next concrete step -- physical Pixel device status (owned yet, or still to buy), how to handle lane_kvm/G0 (host-terminal run matching the existing counsel's own precedent, unaccelerated-in-jail, propose widening the lane, or defer), and confirming the 24.04.4-vs-26.04 OS fact all cross a seam collaboration.mdc names as Claude's-ruling territory rather than mine to decide alone; the one purely mechanical item left -- running tools/generate_jail_local_keys_linux.rish from a real terminal outside the jail -- is Keaton's own hands by design and can happen any time regardless of the other answers.
